### 6.8 Sidebar Animation (global.css)

If your app has a global `* { transition-property: ... }` rule (e.g. for buttons, inputs), it typically excludes `width` and `left`/`right`. That overrides the sidebar's Tailwind `transition-[width]` classes, causing the sidebar to **snap** instead of **animate** when expanding/collapsing.

Add this to `globals.css` (or your main stylesheet) so the sidebar animates smoothly:

```css
/* Sidebar expand/collapse animation - must override global * transition
   (global * excludes width/left/right, so sidebar would snap instead of animate) */
[data-slot="sidebar-gap"],
[data-slot="sidebar-container"] {
  transition-property: width, left, right;
  transition-duration: 200ms;
  transition-timing-function: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
}
```

Place this **after** any global transition rule. The attribute selectors ensure these elements get the correct transition for `width`, `left`, and `right`.

